          <h2>Paddlesports North America Coach Educator Opportunities!</h2>
          <p>Paddlesports North America, in conjunction with British Canoeing has identified a need for Level 1 and 2 Coach Educators in North America. With that in mind, PNA is opening applications for no more than 6, Level 1 and 2 Coach Educators. Applications for Tutor and Assessor roles will be considered from active and updated coaches with a minimum of a Level 3 Qualification or Moderate Water Endorsement.</p>
          <p>The strongest applications will be selected considering the following:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Depth and bredth of coaching qualifications / experience</li>
            <li>Tutoring or teaching qualification/experience</li>
            <li>Assessing qualifications/experience</li>
            <li>Knowledge and understanding of the award syllabus</li>
            <li>Fit to Paddlesports North America workforce demands</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Application packs are available on request from <a href="mailto:fiona.fuller@britishcanoeing.org.uk" target="_blank">fiona.fuller@britishcanoeing.org.uk</a>. The closing date for submission of applications is July 24, 2015.</p>
          <p>Successful applicants will be invited to progress to an orientation on October 6-7, 2015 in Boothbay, ME, after which they will be required to work through an individualized action plan supporting delivery on courses and completing a portfolio of evidence tracking their development.</p>
          <p>For complete information on the Level 1 and 2 Coach Educator descriptions and requirements refer to: <a href="http://paddlesportsnorthamerica.s3.amazonaws.com/downloads/bcuab-coach-educator-requirements-v2-2x.pdf" target="_blank">BCUAB Coach Educator Requirements</a>. The need for Coach Educators will be reviewed periodically and a call for future applicants made in 2016 if identified as needed.</p>
