          <h2>Announcement from the Board</h2>

          <p>The PNA Board is excited to announce that we have finalized our relationship with <abbr title="Formerly known as the British Canoe Union">British Canoeing</abbr> as an Affiliate organization and administrator of Personal Performance programming, and as the Delivery Center for Coaching Qualifications in the United States, Canada and Mexico. With the establishment of the PNA, we will:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>Develop, encourage, train and support coaches to deliver British Canoeing programs on this continent, as well as maintain records of achievement. </li>
            <li>Oversee the delivery of British Canoeing programs and assure high standards are maintained.</li>
            <li>Seek corporate and individual charitable donations to further our mission.</li>
          </ul>

          <p>We are also excited to announce that Paddlesports North America (PNA) is has been classified as an educational public charity under section 501(c)3 of the U.S. Internal Revenue Code.</p>

          <h3>What should you do?</h3>

          <p><strong>Effective September 21, 2014, you should:</strong></p>

          <ul>
            <li>Renew your BCU membership through the PNA. Current rates and forms are available on the PNA website.</li>
            <li>Send all paperwork—including registration forms and fees—to PNA at <%= t('pna.contact.addr_1') %>, <%= t('pna.contact.addr_2') %></li>
          </ul>

          <p>Scott Fairty will be our Interim Administrator and he can be reached at <%= t('pna.contact.email') %> or <%= t('pna.contact.phone.plain') %>.  Please contact Scott for all courses requiring course notification.</p>

          <h2>We need you</h2>

          <p>PNA is a membership organization, and we welcome volunteers to help us as we grow our organization and serve the needs of our members. If you would like to participate in any of the following committees, please contact us at:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>Fundraising</li>
            <li>Membership</li>
            <li>Events</li>
            <li>Sponsorships</li>
            <li>Outreach</li>
            <li>PNA Board of Directors</li>
          </ul>

          <p>More specifically we are looking to fill the position of PNA Administrator.  For a detailed job description please email us at: <a href="mailto:<%= t('pna.contact.email') %>"><%= t('pna.contact.email') %></a></p>

          <h2>Thank you!</h2>

          <p>We are deeply indebted to Bill Lozano, who volunteered his time as the administrator of the BCUNA for the past 13 years. Bill tirelessly handled the paperwork and kept the database for everyone who participated in BCU programming in North America during this period. He worked with several BCU coaches to establish PNA, and helped to broker agreements with British Canoeing to establish PNA as an Affiliate Organization and Delivery Center. He continues to serve as our liaison to British Canoeing. </p>


          <p>Thanks, too, to Mike Devlin, British Canoeing Director of Coaching, for being the chief liaison between PNA and British Canoeing.  Mike has been our guide, helping us navigate through the process of creating the very first Affiliate Organization outside of the United Kingdom.</p>

          <p>We would also like to thank our founding sponsors for their generous support, which covered the expenses incurred in establishing PNA: <a href="http://www.seacliffkayakers.com/" target="_blank">John Carmody of Sea Cliff Kayakers</a>, <a href="http://wernerpaddles.com" target="_blank">Werner Paddles</a>, <a href="http://www.phseakayaks.com/" target="_blank">P&amp;H/Pyranha</a>, <a href="http://seakayakinguk.com" target="_blank">Sea Kayaking UK</a>, <a href="http://www.valleyseakayaks.com/" target="_blank">Valley Sea Kayaks</a> and <a href="http://www.atlantickayaktours.com/" target="_blank">Atlantic Kayak Tours</a>.</p>
